			<ns0:name>evan@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/evan@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We can allow bind/connect from within the sandbox, but in general that is something 
we'd prefer to avoid -- we don't want an exploited renderer to be able to connect to 
the local dbus daemon, etc.

I went to some length to have the browser create sockets on behalf of the renderer in 
the plugin implementation: to open a channel between the renderer and a plugin, the 
browser creates a socketpair, then hands one end to the renderer and one end to the 
plugin.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-03-09T18:32:47.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-03-09T18:32:47.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 1 by evan@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=344#c1" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/344/comments/full/1" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>